<!DOCTYPE rss PUBLIC "-//Netscape Communications//DTD RSS 0.91//EN"
                     "http://my.netscape.com/publish/formats/rss-0.91.dtd"[
<!ENTITY % brandDTD SYSTEM "chrome://global/locale/brand.dtd">%brandDTD;
]>
<rss version="0.91">
  <channel>
    <title>&brandShortName; tips</title>
    <link>http://kompozer.sourceforge.net/</link>
    <description>&brandShortName; tip of the day Archive</description>
    <language>en-us</language>
  
    <item>
      <title>…you can move elements?</title>
      <description>Just place the caret in the block you'd like to move and
                   click once on the Layer button to make the block movable.
      </description>
    </item>
  
    <item>
      <title>…you can customize the toolbars?</title>
      <description>Use the menu "View > Show/Hide > Customize Toolbar" to open
                   the toolbar customization panel. Then use drag and drop to
                   add, move or remove buttons and spaces/separators.
      </description>
    </item>
  
    <item>
      <title>…&brandShortName; has a CSS editor?</title>
      <description>&brandShortName; integrates the CaScadeS CSS editor. Open it using the
                   Tool > CSS Editor menu.</description>
    </item>
  
    <item>
      <title>…&brandShortName; has a Site Manager?</title>
      <description>Use the F9 key or the "View > Show/Hide > Site Manager"
                   menu to show or hide the Site Manager.</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can apply CSS styles to any element?</title>
      <description>Place the caret in the element you wish to style and right-
                   click on the element's tag in the structure toolbar at the
                   bottom of the main window of &brandShortName;. The "Inline styles"
                   menu item will let you style directly that element.
      </description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can control the writing direction?</title>
      <description>Customize your toolbars and add the two direction control
                   buttons.</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can resize table with the mouse?</title>
      <description>Just show the rulers using View > Show/Hide > Rulers and
                   place the caret inside a table cell to see resizers appear.
      </description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can very easily customize a toolbar?</title>
      <description>Just right-click on it…</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you have direct access to the &brandShortName; community?</title>
      <description>Just select the Help > Forums menu entry.</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…&brandShortName; can automatically open a document at launch?</title>
      <description>Use the command-line:      kompozer _your_url_</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can edit more than one site at the same time?</title>
      <description>The Site Manager can open and show the contents of multiple web sites
                   at the same time.</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…&brandShortName; is cross-platform?</title>
      <description>&brandShortName; exists on a wide variety of operating systems, including
                   Windows, Mac OS X, many flavors of Linux, OS/2, …</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can create a new tab with a key combination?</title>
      <description>Control+t (Command+t on Mac OS X) will create a new blank tab</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can create a new window with a key combination?</title>
      <description>Control+shift+n (Command+shift+t on Mac OS X) will create a new blank window</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can change the border of a single table cell?</title>
      <description>Place the caret in that cell, right-click on the cell in the status bar and select Inline Styles &gt; Border tab</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can close a tab with one click?</title>
      <description>Just middle-click on the tab itself</description>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>…you can close the current tab with one key?</title>
      <description>Control-F4 will close the current tab.</description>
    </item>

  </channel>
</rss>

